      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/impl/yangmodels/YangModelSubscriptionEvent.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "I can't use clientId as yang model has an attribute named as \"clientID\", If I do so it would throw \"Unsupported xpath or json data\"\n\nCaused by: org.onap.cps.spi.exceptions.DataValidationException: Failed to parse json data. Unsupported xpath or json data:{\"subscription-registry\":{\"subscription\":[{\"clientId\":\"client id-002\",\"clientName\":\"client-name-sample\",\"isTagged\":false}]}}\n\tat org.onap.cps.utils.YangUtils.parseJsonDataWithOptionalParent(YangUtils.java:194)\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nI followed it from yang model and generated org.onap.cps.ncmp.event.model.Subscription.java\n\n1. avcSubscriptionCreationEvent.json:6\n\n  \"event\": {\n    \"subscription\": {\n      \"clientID\": \"SCO-9989752\",\n      \"name\": \"cm-subscription-001\"\n    },\n\n2. org.onap.cps.ncmp.event.model.Subscription#clientID\n\n    @JsonProperty(\"clientID\")\n    @JsonPropertyDescription(\"The clientID\")\n    private String clientID;\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n@Toine , We are using for example \"org.onap.ncmp.cmhandle.event.lcm.Event#cmHandleId\" as a coding convention and consistency.\n\nIf we want to use \"private String clientId;\", need to update yang model as well. Please suggest",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
